                  <div class="accordion-item">
                    <div class="accordion-header collapsed" data-target="c4" onclick="toggleAccordion(event, 'c4')">
                      COLLABORATION WITH DIRECTORS/PRODUCERS
                      <span class="chev">â–¶</span>
                    </div>
                    <div id="c4" class="accordion-body">
                      <p>R.D. Burman shared distinct and highly successful creative dynamics with directors Nasir Hussain, Ramesh Behl, Gulzar, and Hrishikesh Mukherjee, with each collaboration yielding unique musical outcomes that became iconic in Hindi cinema.</p>

                      <h4>Nasir Hussain</h4>
                      <p>Nasir Hussain and R.D. Burman had a legendary and prolonged partnership, built on a shared vision for modern, youth-oriented musical thrillers and entertainers. Their collaboration, lasting for nine films from the mid-60s to mid-80s, was defined by innovation, techno beats, Western influences, and blockbuster songs that drove the success of the films.</p>

                      <strong>Analysis:</strong>
                      <p>Their work was characterized by catchy, fast-paced songs that often became chartbusters, perfectly complementing Hussain's glossy, escapist cinema style. Burman's use of new instruments and a fresh, energetic sound was revolutionary and instrumental to the films' appeal.</p>

