                      <h4>Hrishikesh Mukherjee</h4>
                      <p>R.D. Burman had an excellent rapport with Hrishikesh Mukherjee, another fellow Bengali filmmaker, and worked on around 11 films with him.</p>
                      <strong>Analysis:</strong>
                      <p>The music in their films was typically light-hearted, situation-based, and integral to the simple, relatable narratives that were Mukherjee's hallmark. The songs had a blend of classic melody and Burman's signature freshness, making them incredibly popular and timeless.</p>

