                      <h4>Dev Anand</h4>
                      <p>R.D. Burman collaborated with Dev Anand on approximately 11 films, a partnership that ushered in a bold, modern, and youth-oriented sound in the 1970s and 1980s, distinguishing itself from the classic melodies of his father, S.D. Burman.</p>

                      <p>The musical partnership between R.D. Burman (Pancham) and Dev Anand was built on mutual respect and a shared desire for innovation. Dev Anand, known for his modern filmmaking approach under the Navketan banner, found that R.D. Burman's experimental style perfectly matched the changing landscape of Hindi cinema in the 70s.</p>

