                    <div id="c7" class="accordion-body">
                      <p>When Pancham entered the music scene, he reshaped the soundscape of modern India. College and youth culture shifted around his rhythms. Students queued outside theatres not for the films, but for his music â€” for the riffs, grooves, flamboyance, and unpredictable brilliance. His songs represented freedom, rebellion, aspiration, and joy.</p>
