                    <div id="c8" class="accordion-body">
                      <p>By the late 1980s, the industry moved toward cheaper synthesizers, formula tracks, and predictable melodies. Panchamâ€™s elaborate, layered arrangements were considered â€œtoo modern,â€ â€œtoo expensive,â€ and â€œtoo experimental.â€</p>
                      <p>Work slowed. Directors hesitated. Trends changed.<br>Musicians recall him saying quietly:</p>
