			<span class="genius-song-block song-1">
				"Tere Bina Jiya Jaye Na (Ghar, 1978)"
					The heartbeat of this soul-melting masterpiece is the Nepali folk percussion instrument, the Madal, transformed by the Boss into a â€˜Madal Tarangâ€™â€”multiple Madal drums tuned at different pitches, creating that hypnotic, ebbing, rhythmic presence that just grabs at your heartstrings. Ranjit Gazmer, the maestro, brought this to life with genius. Supporting percussion like tabla tarang, bongo, conga, triangle, and xylophone weave delicate embellishments while the mellow flute and strings paint warm emotions.
