					Gulzarâ€™s words gently drip with metaphorical longing and quiet despair, enhancing the intimacy.
					Lata Mangeshkarâ€™s rendition is the essence of subtletyâ€”soft, nuanced, holding your breath in tender suspense, perfectly embodying vulnerability.
					The Madal Tarang by Ranjit Gazmer steals the show, anchoring the rhythm with fearless innovation. Alongside him, Manohari Singhâ€™s saxophone, Basu Chakrabortyâ€™s cello, and Maruti Rao Keerâ€™s precise rhythms complete this magical ensemble. The Bossâ€™s sound engineering layered live and double-tracked vocals exquisitely, adding to its timeless aura.
